class Solution {
    private static final int MOD = 1_000_000_007;

    public int numberOfArrays(String s, int k) {
        int n = s.length();
        int[] dp = new int[n + 1];
        dp[n] = 1;

        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == '0') {
                dp[i] = 0;
                continue;
            }
            long num = 0;
            int ways = 0;
            for (int j = i; j < n; j++) {
                num = num * 10 + (s.charAt(j) - '0');
                if (num > k) break;
                ways = (ways + dp[j + 1]) % MOD;
            }
            dp[i] = ways;
        }
        return dp[0];
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log10(k))
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Dynamic programming from right to left. dp[i] counts valid splits starting at index i. For each i, scan forward while the formed number ≤ k, summing dp[j+1]. Early break when number exceeds k. Uses O(n) memory and O(n log10(k)) time due to bounded digit length per split.

